Update on Covid-19 (08th June 2020) 8 June 2020 As of today, the cumulative number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in South Africa is 50 879 Case Data Province Total cases for 8 June 2020 Percentage total Eastern Cape 6341 12,5 Free State 373 0,7 Gauteng 6258 12,3 KwaZulu-Natal 3175 6,2 Limpopo 244 0,5 Mpumalanga 183 0,4 North West 580 1,1 Northern Cape 118 0,2 Western Cape 33568 66,0 Unknown 39 0,1 Total 50879 100,0 Testing Data 943 059 tests have been conducted cumulatively of which 22 983 were conducted since the last report.  Reported COVID-19 Deaths and Recoveries: Regrettably, we report a further 82 COVID-19 related deaths: 55 from Western Cape, 26 from the Eastern Cape, and 1 from KZN. This brings the total national deaths to 1080 with a mortality rate of 2,1%. We extend our condolences to the loved ones of the departed and thank the health care workers who treated the deceased. The recoveries to date are 26 099– this translates to a recovery rate of 51,3%. The provincial breakdown is as follows:eval(ez_write_tag([[300,250],'politicsweb_co_za-box-4','ezslot_4',115,'0','0'])); Province Deaths Recoveries Eastern Cape 127 2666 Free State 9 152 Gauteng 47 2428 KwaZulu Natal 62 1378 Limpopo 3 158 Mpumalanga 1 102 North West 1 73 Northern Cape 1 41 Western Cape 829 19101 Total 1080 26099 Age Distribution Deaths: Age Deaths Percentage 0-9 2 0,2 10-19 3 0,3 20-29 14 1,3 30-39 58 5,4 40-49 126 11,7 50-59 261 24,2 60-69 299 27,7 70-79 201 18,6 80-89 92 8,5 90-99 23 2,1 Uknown 1 0 1080 100 Gender Distribution Deaths: Male (%) Female (%) Total 567 (52,5%) 513 (47,5) 1080 Statement issued by Dr Zwelini Mkhize, Minister of Health, 8 June 2020